WEBVTT

00:00.935 --> 00:02.634
<i> Previously on "nashville"...</i>

00:02.636 --> 00:03.968
Layla: He literally stole
my spotlight.

00:03.970 --> 00:05.970
Jeff: Yeah, well,
it wasn't as bad as you think.

00:05.972 --> 00:08.038
Gabriella: Country is not ready
for a gay star.

00:08.040 --> 00:09.305
Luke:
Your songs are great.

00:09.307 --> 00:11.140
I'd like to put a few of them
on my next album.

00:11.142 --> 00:12.708
No. We're not taking her
off life support.

00:12.710 --> 00:14.176
We have to let her go.

00:16.013 --> 00:17.946
Any time you need help,
I'm your girl.

00:17.948 --> 00:20.648
Juliette:
What'd you do? Just move in
on him the minute I left town?

00:20.650 --> 00:21.849
How dare you!

00:21.851 --> 00:23.217
I don't want to feel
<i> anything.</i>

00:23.219 --> 00:25.118
We're at the hospital,
and our daughter is very sick.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.486
There's someone on the phone
for you.

00:26.488 --> 00:27.386
I don't care.

00:27.388 --> 00:29.121
She said she doesn't care.

00:33.527 --> 00:36.494
[ cap pops ]

00:36.496 --> 00:38.228
[ pills rattle ]

00:40.465 --> 00:41.897
Hey.

00:41.899 --> 00:44.633
The doctor said
the injection site

00:44.635 --> 00:46.201
Might be sore
for a couple days,

00:46.203 --> 00:48.570
So...Here.

00:48.572 --> 00:50.572
This should help.

01:07.490 --> 01:08.722
[ toilet flushes ]

01:19.534 --> 01:21.000
[ sighs ]

01:33.113 --> 01:35.113
It's you and me,
baby girl.

01:35.115 --> 01:37.815
Just you and me.

01:41.053 --> 01:43.086
I think you should go
to natchez.

01:45.090 --> 01:46.789
Baby,
beverly's house is small.

01:46.791 --> 01:48.891
Scarlett can empty it out
by herself.

01:48.893 --> 01:51.158
It's not about scarlett.
It's about you, baby.

01:53.362 --> 01:57.030
You and I,
we've been through so much loss,

01:57.032 --> 01:59.032
And I feel like when
there's unfinished business,

01:59.034 --> 02:00.466
Like with my dad,

02:00.468 --> 02:02.734
It really helped to go
through all that stuff

02:02.736 --> 02:05.603
And it helped me --
helped me say goodbye.

02:12.277 --> 02:13.442
Thanks.

02:13.444 --> 02:16.711
Hadn't changed
since I left.

02:16.713 --> 02:19.547
Didn't think
you'd ever lived here.

02:19.549 --> 02:22.282
Oh, I stayed here a little while
before college.

02:23.785 --> 02:26.218
Slept on this couch.

02:26.220 --> 02:28.987
Anybody coming to help you
with this?

02:28.989 --> 02:29.988
[ purse thuds ]

02:29.990 --> 02:32.724
No, ma'am.
It's just me.

02:32.726 --> 02:33.825
Mm-hmm.

02:33.827 --> 02:34.959
Are you done
with the butter?

02:34.961 --> 02:36.260
Morning, everyone.

02:36.262 --> 02:37.294
Hey.
Hey, emily.

02:37.296 --> 02:38.295
Avery and the baby
aren't down yet?

02:38.297 --> 02:40.730
Oh, rough night.
Coffee's on, though.

02:40.732 --> 02:42.331
Yeah, I'm still here.

02:42.333 --> 02:43.765
Ooh.

02:43.767 --> 02:44.932
Sorry. [ chuckles ]
that's all right.
Go ahead.

02:44.934 --> 02:46.166
Oh, thanks.
I'll see you in 10.

02:46.168 --> 02:47.834
Luke's gonna debut our song
tonight in atlanta.

02:47.836 --> 02:49.335
Congratulations.
Yeah.

02:49.337 --> 02:50.836
He invited us down
to the show.

02:50.838 --> 02:52.571
Me and kevin are gonna
head on down there.

02:52.573 --> 02:54.839
[ cadence crying ]
oh, baby girl,
what's the matter?

02:54.841 --> 02:57.441
Pretty much everything.
She was up most of the night.

02:57.443 --> 02:58.241
It's okay.

02:58.243 --> 02:59.742
No fever, though.

02:59.744 --> 03:02.578
Not sure if it's her ear
acting up again or what.

03:02.580 --> 03:03.745
I got to run, though.

03:03.747 --> 03:05.179
Her, uh, medicine's
on the nightstand.

03:05.181 --> 03:07.247
I don't want to be late
first day on the job.

03:07.249 --> 03:08.248
[ crying continues ]
okay. Good luck.

03:08.250 --> 03:10.016
Well...
Atlanta beckons.

03:10.018 --> 03:11.817
Oh, cadence.

03:11.819 --> 03:13.251
I've always loved that town.
You know what?

03:13.253 --> 03:15.152
You got room in the back
for one more?

03:15.154 --> 03:16.987
[ chuckles ]

03:16.989 --> 03:19.456
Well, I just put my daughter

03:19.458 --> 03:22.258
On a plane to go see
a luke wheeler concert

03:22.260 --> 03:24.426
With her boyfriend.

03:24.428 --> 03:26.161
Yeah.
Maddie will be fine.

03:26.163 --> 03:27.695
I think it's layla
you're gonna need

03:27.697 --> 03:29.096
To be more worried
about today.

03:29.098 --> 03:31.164
Layla will be fine.
What are you talking about?

03:31.166 --> 03:33.299
She can't still be upset about
the whole markus thing, is she?

03:33.301 --> 03:35.267
Yeah, well,
I wish that was the only

03:35.269 --> 03:37.369
Upsetting thing that happened
at the opry last night.

03:37.371 --> 03:39.637
What? What happened?

03:39.639 --> 03:42.106
It's like
I wasn't even there.

03:42.108 --> 03:43.841
Hey, I guarantee you
it'll be a year

03:43.843 --> 03:45.776
Before that guy even gets
an album out.

03:45.778 --> 03:47.344
When yours drops
in a couple of weeks,

03:47.346 --> 03:48.945
All the attention
shifts back to you.

03:48.947 --> 03:50.813
Bucky said that rayna still
had a lot of thoughts

03:50.815 --> 03:53.182
About my album,
which doesn't sound good.

03:53.184 --> 03:54.650
Look, your stuff is great.

03:54.652 --> 03:56.952
Yeah, but she's rayna jaymes.
She's literally a living legend.

03:56.954 --> 03:58.620
Listen to me --
the myth of rayna jaymes

03:58.622 --> 04:00.855
Is just that -- a myth.

04:00.857 --> 04:02.056
Just listen to her notes.

04:02.058 --> 04:03.357
If you like them, take them,

04:03.359 --> 04:05.292
And if you don't,
well, then don't.

04:05.294 --> 04:07.460
I wish you didn't
have to go to atlanta.

04:09.797 --> 04:12.130
Oh. Since when
do you wear a tie?

04:12.132 --> 04:13.931
Well, sometimes you got to
look professional.

04:24.042 --> 04:26.208
So, when's
the wining and dining start?

04:26.210 --> 04:27.809
Pretty much
as soon as we land.

04:27.811 --> 04:29.177
Now, I've lined up
about a dozen

04:29.179 --> 04:31.145
Potential brand partners
for us to meet with.

04:31.147 --> 04:33.213
We're talking
big corporate entities here,

04:33.215 --> 04:35.248
So I hope you are ready
to wow them

04:35.250 --> 04:36.916
With the luke wheeler
experience.

04:36.918 --> 04:38.684
Oh, I'm an experience,
am I?

04:38.686 --> 04:40.018
You have been for<i> me.</i>

04:40.020 --> 04:41.753
Now, let's talk about
the c.E.O. Search.

04:41.755 --> 04:43.721
This is the short list
I've narrowed it down to,

04:43.723 --> 04:45.823
Which we are vetting.

04:45.825 --> 04:48.058
You never talked to me much
about what happened at deacon's.

04:48.060 --> 04:49.426
Oh, it's nothing.

04:49.428 --> 04:51.194
Some people just aren't
who you thought they were.

04:51.196 --> 04:53.396
It's so lame
I can't stay the night.

04:53.398 --> 04:54.830
My mom's just so paranoid.

04:54.832 --> 04:56.698
She thinks if we stay
in the same hotel that we'd --

04:56.700 --> 04:58.066
We'd do it.

04:58.068 --> 04:59.901
Shh!
[ laughs ]

04:59.903 --> 05:02.837
It's not like
we're gonna be alone, anyway.

05:02.839 --> 05:03.871
Mm.

05:03.873 --> 05:05.973
Maybe we<i> could</i> be.

05:07.076 --> 05:10.110
I cannot believe I fell
for this tabloid crap.

05:10.112 --> 05:12.078
I mean, I must have been
out of my mind.

05:12.080 --> 05:14.380
There's nothing going on
between avery and emily.

05:14.382 --> 05:16.615
I know them.
They wouldn't do that.

05:16.617 --> 05:17.882
<i> I'm</i> capable of anything,

05:17.884 --> 05:21.384
But they're better people
than...

05:21.386 --> 05:22.385
That.

05:22.387 --> 05:25.087
[ clears throat ]

05:25.089 --> 05:28.223
So, um,
I was reading this article,

05:28.225 --> 05:29.891
Um, about body language,

05:29.893 --> 05:32.393
And the way
their faces are turned

05:32.395 --> 05:33.761
Means they're having sex.

05:33.763 --> 05:35.963
Do you even listen to yourself
when you talk?

05:35.965 --> 05:37.798
You are so funny.

05:37.800 --> 05:40.000
I'm gonna go get my stuff.

05:54.382 --> 05:55.781
Excuse me.

05:55.783 --> 05:57.949
I have
a messenger coming by

05:57.951 --> 06:00.217
To pick up some
legal paperwork for me.
[ cellphone dings ]

06:00.219 --> 06:01.551
Can I leave it with you?

06:01.553 --> 06:03.386
Sure. No problem.

06:03.388 --> 06:06.889
Actually, um...
You can hold off on that.

06:12.596 --> 06:15.263
¶¶

06:23.105 --> 06:25.605
So, I guess we're gonna see
juliette tonight,

06:25.607 --> 06:27.773
But I reckon we avoid her,
on behalf of avery.

06:27.775 --> 06:29.941
[ scoffs ]
man, that's got to suck --

06:29.943 --> 06:32.476
Being in love with somebody
who doesn't want you around.

06:32.478 --> 06:34.411
Yep.

06:34.413 --> 06:36.112
How about you, gunnar?
How's your love life?

06:36.114 --> 06:37.680
Any new girls around?
Or old ones?

06:37.682 --> 06:39.148
You hook up with zoey
while she was in town?

06:39.150 --> 06:41.350
Nah, she's dating somebody
in l.A.,

06:41.352 --> 06:44.853
But had a spark with emily
this morning over the milk.

06:44.855 --> 06:47.856
We touched hands,
and, well...

06:47.858 --> 06:49.157
Well, if that's all
that it takes,

06:49.159 --> 06:50.258
Then<i> I</i> had a spark
with emily, too.

06:50.260 --> 06:51.325
[ chuckles ]
no, really.

06:51.327 --> 06:52.326
I-I think she's into me.

06:52.328 --> 06:53.360
First of all,
no, she's not.

06:53.362 --> 06:55.462
Second of all,
that's a terrible idea.

06:55.464 --> 06:57.330
What's wrong with emily?
She's -- she's totally hot.

06:57.332 --> 06:58.964
She's nice, she --
she's your roommate's nanny.

06:58.966 --> 07:00.765
All right, forget the nanny,
forget nashville.

07:00.767 --> 07:02.633
New trip objective --

07:02.635 --> 07:03.700
Get gunnar laid.

07:03.702 --> 07:06.002
[ laughs ]

07:06.004 --> 07:07.269
Over a month goes by.

07:07.271 --> 07:09.671
She leaves town,
changes her phone number,

07:09.673 --> 07:12.440
Doesn't take an emergency call
from me about our daughter,

07:12.442 --> 07:13.974
And<i> now</i> she texts me?

07:13.976 --> 07:15.508
I don't get it.
[ sighs ]

07:15.510 --> 07:17.176
What is this,
some kind of weird sixth sense?

07:17.178 --> 07:18.944
I mean, does she know
I signed the divorce papers?

07:18.946 --> 07:20.211
Did you?

07:20.213 --> 07:21.345
I haven't set them off yet,
but yeah.

07:21.347 --> 07:22.713
Hey, what's up, guys?
I'm markus.

07:22.715 --> 07:24.381
Whatever. I can't deal with this
right now.

07:24.383 --> 07:25.715
I got to go. Markus is here.
I'll call you later.

07:25.717 --> 07:27.283
Okay.
Yo, yo, yo!

07:27.285 --> 07:29.518
I am so sorry I am --

07:29.520 --> 07:30.719
[ chuckling ]
wow -- an hour late.

07:30.721 --> 07:31.720
My bad.

07:31.722 --> 07:33.121
Yo.
How's the baby, man?

07:33.123 --> 07:34.822
Good. Good.
Thanks for asking.

07:34.824 --> 07:37.491
Listen, I am really excited
to be doing this with you.

07:37.493 --> 07:39.793
Please, dude.
It's on me -- seriously.

07:39.795 --> 07:41.628
I can tell you're
a no-b.S. Kind of guy,

07:41.630 --> 07:42.996
And that's what I want
in a producer, you know?

07:42.998 --> 07:44.197
So just shoot me straight,

07:44.199 --> 07:45.998
Call it how you see it,
and we're golden.

07:46.000 --> 07:47.733
Okay.
I'm up for the challenge.

07:47.735 --> 07:48.633
Cool, man.
Want to get started?

07:48.635 --> 07:49.634
Yeah.
Huh?

07:49.636 --> 07:50.635
Hey, guys, I'm markus.

07:50.637 --> 07:51.502
<i> Hey, it's emily.</i>
<i> Leave a message.</i>

07:51.504 --> 07:52.736
[ beep ]

07:52.738 --> 07:54.003
I shouldn't have
yelled at you like that.

07:54.005 --> 07:56.071
I don't know
what I was thinking.

07:56.073 --> 07:59.374
I just would really like
to talk to you...

07:59.376 --> 08:01.142
Or to avery.

08:01.144 --> 08:02.877
[ clatter ]
dude!

08:02.879 --> 08:05.546
That bag costs more than
you make in, like, two years.

08:05.548 --> 08:07.114
I mean, am I right?

08:08.817 --> 08:11.184
I miss you.

08:11.186 --> 08:14.086
Just call me back --
please.

08:17.757 --> 08:19.356
Luke:
Everybody smile.

08:19.358 --> 08:20.690
[ camera clicks ]
okay.

08:20.692 --> 08:22.191
I'm sending that
to your mom

08:22.193 --> 08:23.859
To show her what a good time
we're having.

08:23.861 --> 08:25.227
Uh, what time
are we leaving?

08:25.229 --> 08:26.561
Uh, we'll probably head
to the arena

08:26.563 --> 08:27.728
In about a half-hour
or so.

08:27.730 --> 08:29.229
Is it all right
if I get changed here?

08:29.231 --> 08:30.597
I brought something else
to wear tonight.

08:30.599 --> 08:31.831
Yeah, it's fine.
You can use colt's room.

08:31.833 --> 08:34.166
Okay.

08:34.168 --> 08:35.567
[ knock ]
gabriella: Hey.

08:35.569 --> 08:37.035
I'm sorry --
I don't mean to interrupt,

08:37.037 --> 08:39.370
But I just got a call
from ethan baker from coca-cola.

08:39.372 --> 08:41.205
He'd love to have a drink
with you downstairs.

08:41.207 --> 08:42.739
Um...

08:42.741 --> 08:44.340
Yeah.
It's fine, dad.

08:44.342 --> 08:45.741
Just let us know when you're
ready, and we'll head down.

08:45.743 --> 08:47.743
Okay. I want you to head down
the minute maddie is dressed.

08:47.745 --> 08:48.777
How about that?
Yes, sir.

08:48.779 --> 08:49.744
Okay.

08:51.781 --> 08:53.313
So sorry.
No, no.

08:59.286 --> 09:00.651
[ breathes deeply ]

09:03.422 --> 09:04.921
[ sighs ] didn't expect
to see<i> you</i> here.

09:04.923 --> 09:07.056
Jumped on
a last-minute flight.

09:07.058 --> 09:08.457
What are you doing?
[ sighs ]

09:08.459 --> 09:11.126
Keep...Donate...
Throw away.

09:11.128 --> 09:12.627
Just trying to figure out
where everything goes.

09:12.629 --> 09:14.228
"keep" pile
ain't too big, is it?

09:14.230 --> 09:16.129
Well, mama had a habit
of saving things

09:16.131 --> 09:17.130
That didn't need saving.

09:18.766 --> 09:20.599
Being as you and I don't see
eye to eye on these things,

09:20.601 --> 09:22.867
I think maybe I better
take a look around, huh?

09:24.470 --> 09:25.836
I'll start in the bedroom.

09:30.642 --> 09:32.441
[ sighs ]

09:32.443 --> 09:34.976
Will lexington's
been dropped,

09:34.978 --> 09:37.144
You spent days in new york
with luke taking meetings,

09:37.146 --> 09:39.212
And now you're both here
talking to coca-cola and ford.

09:39.214 --> 09:41.047
Let me guess --
you're gearing up

09:41.049 --> 09:43.315
To launch a luke wheeler
lifestyle brand.

09:43.317 --> 09:45.417
If you're looking
for your client,

09:45.419 --> 09:47.719
She just left
for the arena.

09:47.721 --> 09:49.887
Actually,
I'm here for<i> you.</i>

09:49.889 --> 09:53.490
Look, I know you are quietly
running a c.E.O. Search.

09:53.492 --> 09:54.791
I want to be
on that list.

09:54.793 --> 09:55.992
Don't you
already have a job?

09:55.994 --> 09:57.560
I'd be better
at<i> this</i> one.

09:57.562 --> 09:59.929
I'm gonna tell you why
the people you're
looking at won't work.

09:59.931 --> 10:01.297
Phil diamond
has a mistress,

10:01.299 --> 10:03.465
Dave burns has an on-again/
off-again cocaine habit,

10:03.467 --> 10:06.568
And steve whitaker likes
to vacation in thailand --

10:06.570 --> 10:07.936
A lot.

10:07.938 --> 10:11.005
That's your short list,
right?

10:11.007 --> 10:12.806
Hey, luke.

10:12.808 --> 10:14.007
Hey, jeff.
How you doing?

10:14.009 --> 10:15.408
Michael.
Good to see you, man.

10:15.410 --> 10:16.675
It's been years
since cannes.

10:16.677 --> 10:17.842
Michael:
Good to see you, jeff.

10:17.844 --> 10:19.076
What,
you two know each other?

10:19.078 --> 10:20.477
Oh, yeah.
We go way back.
Yeah.

10:20.479 --> 10:23.112
I know this guy, too.
How you doing, dave?
Great.

10:23.114 --> 10:25.180
Hey, your daughter
still rowing crew at yale?

10:25.182 --> 10:28.149
So, my favorite room
in the house -- come on in.

10:28.151 --> 10:29.450
Oh, wow.
[ chuckles ]

10:29.452 --> 10:31.318
Oh, this is great!

10:31.320 --> 10:32.919
Well, I'm so happy
to have you here.

10:32.921 --> 10:34.487
Hey, by the way,
bucky told me

10:34.489 --> 10:36.455
That you might have been
a little bit upset

10:36.457 --> 10:38.423
About what happened
with markus last night.

10:38.425 --> 10:40.091
That's okay.
I just want to say,

10:40.093 --> 10:41.959
There is no way
that that could take away

10:41.961 --> 10:44.494
From how wonderful
your performance was.

10:44.496 --> 10:46.329
Well, thanks.

10:46.331 --> 10:48.864
Yeah, bucky said that you had
some thoughts about the album?

10:48.866 --> 10:50.665
A few little things,
you know?

10:50.667 --> 10:52.600
I think we could make
a couple tweaks here and there.

10:52.602 --> 10:54.868
Cool.
Uh, maybe go
a little bit deeper.

10:54.870 --> 10:56.202
Oh.

10:56.204 --> 10:57.603
Well, I mean,
just so you know,

10:57.605 --> 11:00.639
My manager and I are both
really happy with this album.

11:00.641 --> 11:02.507
I mean, jeff loves it.

11:02.509 --> 11:04.141
I want to ask you something
about jeff.

11:04.143 --> 11:05.308
Sure.

11:05.310 --> 11:06.709
Is there something going on
with y'all?

11:06.711 --> 11:09.478
'cause bucky mentioned
last night at the opry that --

11:09.480 --> 11:11.379
Yeah, I mean,
we've been dating.

11:11.381 --> 11:12.880
Oh.

11:12.882 --> 11:14.781
Is that
gonna be a problem?

11:14.783 --> 11:15.848
Well, listen,
I would be lying

11:15.850 --> 11:17.716
If I said I did not have
a problem with jeff.

11:17.718 --> 11:19.551
I had a problem with him
being your manager,

11:19.553 --> 11:20.952
But as your boyfriend?

11:20.954 --> 11:22.353
I just --
I don't really understand.

11:22.355 --> 11:24.722
Is that why you brought me here?
Is that what this is about?

11:24.724 --> 11:26.657
No.
Of course not.

11:26.659 --> 11:27.658
Let's look at the music.

11:27.660 --> 11:29.559
Great.

11:29.561 --> 11:31.127
[ sighs ]

11:33.698 --> 11:35.030
[ chuckles ]
wow!

11:35.032 --> 11:36.197
[ laughs ]

11:36.199 --> 11:37.464
You look great.

11:37.466 --> 11:39.032
Thank you.
Where's your dad?

11:39.034 --> 11:41.467
Uh, he's downstairs,
meeting with people.

11:41.469 --> 11:42.868
Does that mean
we're alone?

11:44.671 --> 11:47.204
Uh...Yeah, but...

11:47.206 --> 11:48.738
Do you want to go
downstairs, or...

11:55.312 --> 11:57.478
Maybe, um...

11:57.480 --> 11:59.646
Maybe we shouldn't do this
right now.

12:00.448 --> 12:02.481
Yeah. Okay.

